# Audio Channel Layout Tags

**API Collection**

The identifiers that represent audio channel layouts.

## Overview

Use these values to set the [doc://com.apple.coreaudiotypes/documentation/CoreAudioTypes/AudioChannelLayout/mChannelLayoutTag] field of an [doc://com.apple.coreaudiotypes/documentation/CoreAudioTypes/AudioChannelLayout] structure.

## General Layouts

- **kAudioChannelLayoutTag_UseChannelDescriptions**: An array of audio channel description structures that defines the layout mapping.
- **kAudioChannelLayoutTag_UseChannelBitmap**: A bitmap that defines the layout mapping.
- **kAudioChannelLayoutTag_Mono**: A standard monophonic stream.
- **kAudioChannelLayoutTag_Stereo**: A standard stereophonic stream.
- **kAudioChannelLayoutTag_StereoHeadphones**: A standard stereo stream; headphone playback implied.
- **kAudioChannelLayoutTag_MatrixStereo**: A matrix-encoded stereo stream.
- **kAudioChannelLayoutTag_MidSide**: A middle and side channel audio layout.
- **kAudioChannelLayoutTag_XY**: A coincident, angled microphone pair.
- **kAudioChannelLayoutTag_Binaural**: A binaural stereo audio layout.
- **kAudioChannelLayoutTag_Ambisonic_B_Format**: An ambisonic B-format audio layout.
- **kAudioChannelLayoutTag_Quadraphonic**: A quadraphonic audio layout.
- **kAudioChannelLayoutTag_Pentagonal**: A pentalgonal audio layout.
- **kAudioChannelLayoutTag_Hexagonal**: A hexagonal audio layout.
- **kAudioChannelLayoutTag_Octagonal**: An octagonal audio layout.
- **kAudioChannelLayoutTag_Cube**: A cubic audio layout.

## Accessing the Data

- **mChannelBitmap**: If `mChannelLayoutTag` is set to `kAudioChannelLayoutTag_UseChannelBitmap`, this field is the channel-use bitmap.
- **AudioChannelBitmap**: The supported channel bitmaps to use when defining channel layouts.
- **mChannelDescriptions**: A variable length array of `mNumberChannelDescription` elements that describes a layout. If the `mChannelLayoutTag` field is set to `kAudioChannelLayoutTag_UseChannelDescriptions`, use this field to describe the layout.
- **mChannelLayoutTag**: The `AudioChannelLayoutTag` value that indicates the layout. See [doc://com.apple.coreaudiotypes/documentation/CoreAudioTypes/audio-channel-layout-tags] for possible values.
- **AudioChannelLayoutTag**: Identifies a previously-defined channel layout.
- **mNumberChannelDescriptions**: The number of items in the `mChannelDescriptions` array.
- **AudioChannelLayoutTag_GetNumberOfChannels(_:)**: Retrieves the number of channels from an audio channel layout tag.
